The Igbo Delegates Assembly (IDA) in the 19 Northern states and the Federal Capital Territory (FCT), has again urged the  All Progressives Congress (APC),  the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) and other political parties in the country to zone their presidential slots to the  Southeast. The IDA  comprises executive members from in the  19 Northern states and the FCT, Ndi Eze Igbo (Igbo traditional rulers) , Northern (Hausa/ Fulani) leaders in the Southeast as well as critical and eminent Igbo stakeholders in the North. The appeal was contained in a statement by the assembly at the end of its meeting in Abuja yesterday. The statement was signed by Chief Chikezie Nwogu, president-general of the assembly;  Austin Ifedinezi, secretary-general; Pampas Nwahiwu, president, Ndieze Igbo in the North and  Boniface Ibekwe , president, Eze Igbo in the Diaspora. According to the statement, the IDA  emphasised the need  for  unity  of  and oneness in the country.   Presidential ticket: ‘why APC can’t use consensus’     Wike to delegates: Compensate me for sustaining PDP     INEC publishes final list of Osun Gov candidates   The statement reads in part: ‘We  reinstated that Ndigbo believe in   one united and indivisible Nigeria where equity, justice, peace, love and fairness reign supreme. “Also, we  reinstated our sincere appeal to Nigerians of all ethnicities, geopolitical zones, religious, traditional institutions, all the political parties to zone the Presidency of Nigeria, come 2023, to the  Southeast  for the interest of peace, love, equity, justice and rapid progress of Nigeria.” The IDA also appealed to all leadership strata in Nigeria country to emulate the peaceful, brotherly love, understanding and synergy that the leadership of Ndigbo in the North and the leadership of Northerners in the Southeast enjoy today. The assembly praised President Muhammadu Buhari for signing the Electoral Act  and   urged the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) to do the needful by improving on the application of BVAS and other necessary areas to avoid the lapses encountered in previous elections It urged  every Igbo who has attained the age of 18  and above to register and secure his PVC ahead of the 2023 general election.